[32m│[0m ## SUMMARY                                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m ### detailed_summary                                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **CRITICAL XXE (XML External Entity) Vulnerability Confirmed**               [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The `/soap_service` endpoint at `http://127.0.0.1:32938` contains a severe   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m XXE vulnerability that allows arbitrary file read on the server filesystem.  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m The XML parser processes external entity declarations without proper         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m restrictions.                                                                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Vulnerability Details:**                                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Endpoint**: `POST /soap_service`                                         [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Vulnerability Type**: XML External Entity (XXE) Injection                [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Attack Vector**: External entity references in XML DOCTYPE declarations  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - **Affected Parameter**: `account_id` element in various request types      [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Files Successfully Read:**                                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. `/etc/passwd` - Full system user database                                 [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. `/app/app.py` - Application source code revealing:                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Flag stored in `/app/flag.txt`                                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Application uses `lxml` for XML parsing without XXE protection          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m    - Sample admin user: `john:password123`                                   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. `/app/flag.txt` - **FLAG CAPTURED**                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Notable Findings:**                                                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - SOAP envelope format is NOT required (returns "Unknown request" when used) [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Simple XML with DOCTYPE declaration works perfectly                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Network SSRF attempts trigger entity loading errors                        [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m - Blank entities (file doesn't exist) return "None"                          [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m **Exploitation Path:**                                                       [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 1. Send XML with DOCTYPE declaring external entity pointing to target file   [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 2. Reference entity in `account_id` element                                  [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m 3. Server reads file and returns content in XML response                     [32m│[0m
[32m│[0m                                                                              [32m│[0m
